.TH GRAFANA-UTIL-DATASOURCE-IMPORT 1 "2026-04-03" "grafana-util 0.7.4" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
grafana\-util\-datasource\-import \- Import datasource inventory through the Grafana API.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B grafana-util datasource import [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Import datasource inventory through the Grafana API.
.PP
Use this when you have a local datasource bundle or provisioning tree and want to push it into Grafana, either live or as a dry run.
.SH COMMON OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-import\-dir
source path for inventory or provisioning input.
.TP
.B \-\-input\-format
choose inventory or provisioning.
.TP
.B \-\-org\-id, \-\-use\-export\-org, \-\-only\-org\-id, \-\-create\-missing\-orgs
control cross\-org routing.
.TP
.B \-\-replace\-existing, \-\-update\-existing\-only, \-\-require\-matching\-export\-org
import safety and reconciliation controls.
.TP
.B \-\-secret\-values
resolve placeholder secrets during import.
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run, \-\-table, \-\-json, \-\-output\-format, \-\-no\-header, \-\-output\-columns, \-\-progress, \-\-verbose
preview and reporting controls.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Import datasource inventory through the Grafana API.
.EX
grafana-util datasource import --url http://localhost:3000 --basic-user admin --basic-password admin --import-dir ./datasources --dry-run --table
.EE
.PP
Import datasource inventory through the Grafana API.
.EX
grafana-util datasource import --url http://localhost:3000 --basic-user admin --basic-password admin --import-dir ./datasources --use-export-org --only-org-id 2 --create-missing-orgs --dry-run --json
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBgrafana-util\fR(1),
\fBgrafana-util-datasource\fR(1)
